# Calculate shovel hours and dumper hours
shovel_hours = final_filter_shovel["Selected Duration Idle Hrs."] + final_filter_shovel["Selected Duration Work Hrs."]
dumper_hours = final_filter_dumper["Selected Duration Idle Hrs."] + final_filter_dumper["Selected Duration Work Hrs."]

shovel_hours.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
dumper_hours.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

# Function to find the combination of 3 dumpers whose sum is closest to the shovel hours
def find_closest_combination(shovel_index, used_combinations, used_dumpers):
    shovel_target = shovel_hours[shovel_index]
    min_diff = float('inf')
    best_combination = None

    # Generate combinations of 3 dumpers excluding used ones
    for comb in combinations([d for d in range(len(dumper_hours)) if d not in used_dumpers], 3):
        total = sum(dumper_hours[d] for d in comb)
        if total >= shovel_target:  # Ensure the sum of dumpers is greater than or equal to shovel hours
            diff = total - shovel_target
            if diff < min_diff:
                min_diff = diff
                best_combination = comb
    
    if best_combination is not None:
        # Add the best combination to used combinations and update used dumpers
        used_combinations.add(best_combination)
        used_dumpers.update(best_combination)
    
    return best_combination

# Assign dumpers to each shovel
assignments = {}
used_combinations = set()
used_dumpers = set()
# Sort shovels based on shovel hours in ascending order
shovel_indices_sorted = sorted(range(len(shovel_hours)), key=lambda k: shovel_hours[k])
for i in shovel_indices_sorted:
    closest_combination = find_closest_combination(i, used_combinations, used_dumpers)
    if closest_combination is not None:
        assignments[i+1] = [d+1 for d in closest_combination]  # Add 1 to convert index to dumper number

# Print allotments with indices
print("Allotments:")
for shovel, dumpers in assignments.items():
    shovel_index = shovel - 1
    shovel_hour = shovel_hours[shovel_index]
    print(f"Shovel {shovel_index} (Idle hrs. + working hrs.: {shovel_hour:.2f}):")
    for dumper in dumpers:
        dumper_index = dumper - 1
        dumper_hour = dumper_hours[dumper_index]
        print(f"  Dumper {dumper_index} (Idle hrs. + working hrs.: {dumper_hour:.2f})")
